# Performance

## Definition

Performance describes how efficiently a system uses CPU time, memory, storage, and power while satisfying timing requirements.

---

## Why It Matters

Poor performance can result in:

- Missed deadlines
- Increased latency
- Unnecessary power consumption
- Reduced system responsiveness

---

## Design Techniques Covered

- Static Allocation
- Memory Pools
- Event-Driven Design
- RTOS Architecture
- Efficient Scheduling


